author: Justin Roberts
title: A frigid Friday morning but warmer weather is en route! - NewsBreak
text:
By Justin Roberts ,
39 minutes ago OTTUMWA, Iowa (KYOU) - A much different scene this morning from yesterday morning as the day starts with single digits and wind chills near zero if not below. Look for partly sunny skies and highs warming to the mid and upper 20s. A slow warming trend shapes up with temps only dropping to the low 20s overnight into Saturday, before another cold front brings another briefly colder air mass. The weekend is dry with temps varying from the 30s to lower 40s. Significantly warmer temperatures are likely next week with the warmest day of the week now slated for Christmas Day.
